{"title_page": "W. Dabney Stuart", "text_new": "'''Walker Dabney Stuart III''' (born November 4, 1937 [[Richmond, Virginia]]) is an American [[poet]].<ref>http://www.poetryfoundation.org/archive/poet.html?id=6640</ref><ref>http://www.jrank.org/literature/pages/10101/Dabney-Stuart.html</ref>\n\nHe graduated from [[Davidson College]], with a BA in English in 1960, and from [[Harvard University]], with an MA in English in 1962.\n<ref>Stalling, Mary Bartram. [http://www.encyclopediavirginia.org/Stuart_Dabney_1937- \"Dabney Stuart (1937\u2013 ).\"] ''Encyclopedia Virginia''. Ed. Brendan Wolfe. 17 June 2009</ref>\nHe is professor emeritus of English at [[Washington and Lee University]].<ref>http://www.vqronline.org/author/5063/dabney-stuart/</ref>\nHis work appeared in ''Poetry,<ref>http://www.poetryfoundation.org/archive/poem.html?id=171192</ref> Shenandoah, Southern Review, and Yale Review''.\n\n==Awards==\n*1987 [[Guggenheim Fellowship]] <ref>http://www.gf.org/fellows/14329-w-dabney-stuart</ref>\n\n==Works==\n\n===Poetry===\n*''Tables'', Pinyon Publishing, 2009, {{ISBN|978-0-9821561-1-7}}\n*''Family preserve: poems'', University of Virginia Press, 2005, {{ISBN|978-0-8139-2328-4}}\n*[https://books.google.com/books?id=7AnnubIXhkMC&printsec=frontcover&dq=inauthor:Dabney+inauthor:Stuart&lr=&as_brr=0&ei=O7_7S-2BOZm2Mvn-jPAN&cd=4#v=onepage&q&f=false ''The man who loves C\u00e9zanne: poems''], LSU Press, 2003, {{ISBN|978-0-8071-2900-5}}\n*''Settlers: poems'', Louisiana State University Press, 1999, {{ISBN|978-0-8071-2406-2}}\n*''Long gone: poems'', Louisiana State University Press, 1996, {{ISBN|978-0-8071-2121-4}}\n*''Light years: new and selected poems'', Louisiana State University Press, 1994, {{ISBN|978-0-8071-1898-6}}\n*''Narcissus dreaming: poems'', Louisiana State University Press, 1990, {{ISBN|978-0-8071-1591-6}}\n*''Don't look back: poems'', Louisiana State University Press, 1987, {{ISBN|978-0-8071-1374-5}}\n*''Common ground: poems'', Louisiana State University Press, 1982, {{ISBN|978-0-8071-1023-2}}\n*''Round and round: a triptych : poems'', Louisiana University Press, 1977, {{ISBN|978-0-8071-0271-8}}\n*''The other hand: poems'', Louisiana State University Press, 1974, {{ISBN|978-0-8071-0076-9}}\n*''A particular place; poems'', Knopf, 1969\n\n===Stories===\n*[https://books.google.com/books?id=h55Hz0IKFjkC&printsec=frontcover&dq=inauthor:Dabney+inauthor:Stuart&lr=&as_drrb_is=q&as_minm_is=0&as_miny_is=&as_maxm_is=0&as_maxy_is=&as_brr=0&ei=3L77S8Iekfoz0bG52As&cd=1#v=onepage&q&f=false ''No visible means of support: stories''], University of Missouri Press, 2001, {{ISBN|978-0-8262-1320-4}}\n*[https://books.google.com/books?id=ZHtpDoR2E7cC&pg=PA148&lpg=PA148&dq=W.+Dabney+Stuart&source=bl&ots=J1qY-QCwnV&sig=RP9VigueYSVKXECihNcUcoIhF18&hl=en&ei=ejX7S7PqGIGdlgeFvNnZDw&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=5&ved=0CCQQ6AEwBA#v=onepage&q&f=false ''The way to Cobbs Creek: stories''], University of Missouri Press, 1997, {{ISBN|978-0-8262-1143-9}}\n\n===Criticism===\n*''Nabokov: The Dimensions of Parody'', Louisiana State University Press, 1978, {{ISBN|978-0-8071-0384-5}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://books.google.com/books?id=xxd451POnpYC&pg=PA388&dq=W.+Dabney+Stuart+poet&hl=en&ei=TL77S6WuKoO8lQeZ84XqDw&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&ved=0CCsQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=W.%20Dabney%20Stuart%20poet&f=false \"Dabney Stuart\"], ''Southern writers: a new biographical dictionary'', Editors Joseph M. Flora, Amber Vogel, Bryan Albin Giemza, LSU Press, 2006, {{ISBN|978-0-8071-3123-7}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Stuart, W. Dabney}}\n[[Category:American male poets]]\n[[Category:1937 births]]\n[[Category:Writers from Richmond, Virginia]]\n[[Category:Guggenheim Fellows]]\n[[Category:Davidson College alumni]]\n[[Category:Harvard University alumni]]\n[[Category:Washington and Lee University faculty]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "'''Walker Dabney Stuart III''' (born November 4, 1937 [[Richmond, Virginia]]) is an American [[poet]].<ref>http://www.poetryfoundation.org/archive/poet.html?id=6640</ref><ref>http://www.jrank.org/literature/pages/10101/Dabney-Stuart.html</ref>\n\nHe graduated from [[Davidson College]], with a BA in English in 1960, and from [[Harvard University]], with an MA in English in 1962.\n<ref>Stalling, Mary Bartram. [http://www.encyclopediavirginia.org/Stuart_Dabney_1937- \"Dabney Stuart (1937\u2013 ).\"] ''Encyclopedia Virginia''. Ed. Brendan Wolfe. 17 June 2009</ref>\nHe is professor emeritus of English at [[Washington and Lee University]].<ref>http://www.vqronline.org/author/5063/dabney-stuart/</ref>\nHis work appeared in ''Poetry,<ref>http://www.poetryfoundation.org/archive/poem.html?id=171192</ref> Shenandoah, Southern Review, and Yale Review''.\n\n==Awards==\n*1987 [[Guggenheim Fellowship]] <ref>http://www.gf.org/fellows/14329-w-dabney-stuart</ref>\n\n==Works==\n\n===Poetry===\n*''Tables'', Pinyon Publishing, 2009, {{ISBN|978-0-9821561-1-7}}\n*''Family preserve: poems'', University of Virginia Press, 2005, {{ISBN|978-0-8139-2328-4}}\n*[https://books.google.com/books?id=7AnnubIXhkMC&printsec=frontcover&dq=inauthor:Dabney+inauthor:Stuart&lr=&as_brr=0&ei=O7_7S-2BOZm2Mvn-jPAN&cd=4#v=onepage&q&f=false ''The man who loves C\u00e9zanne: poems''], LSU Press, 2003, {{ISBN|978-0-8071-2900-5}}\n*''Settlers: poems'', Louisiana State University Press, 1999, {{ISBN|978-0-8071-2406-2}}\n*''Long gone: poems'', Louisiana State University Press, 1996, {{ISBN|978-0-8071-2121-4}}\n*''Light years: new and selected poems'', Louisiana State University Press, 1994, {{ISBN|978-0-8071-1898-6}}\n*''Narcissus dreaming: poems'', Louisiana State University Press, 1990, {{ISBN|978-0-8071-1591-6}}\n*''Don't look back: poems'', Louisiana State University Press, 1987, {{ISBN|978-0-8071-1374-5}}\n*''Common ground: poems'', Louisiana State University Press, 1982, {{ISBN|978-0-8071-1023-2}}\n*''Round and round: a triptych : poems'', Louisiana University Press, 1977, {{